Adds missing support data for <meta name="viewport">.

This PR assumes that Mobile Safari 3 for iOS shipped the first <meta name="viewport"> implementation, and all later released mobile browsers followed.

  • Firefox 4 for Android
  • Chrome 18 for Android
  • Opera Mobile 10

Thereâ€™s a viewport-fit feature that Safari 11 presumably shipped. I just learned that Chrome is planning to ship it soon, too.

items.content_html:
Summary

the support for URLSearchParams class is:

  • v7.0.0 - added as an internal instance (can be accessed via URL.prototype.searchParams)
    • constructor
    • append
    • delete
    • set
    • get
    • getAll
    • has
    • toString
    • @@iterator
  • v7.3.0 - exposed via url module, URL.prototype.searchParams no longer returns an empty list
    • keys
    • values
    • forEach
    • entries
  • v7.5.0 - extra support for constructor
    • constructor support a USVString
  • v7.7.0 - support sort() method
  • v7.10.0 - extra support for constructor
    • constructor support a record or sequence
  • v6.13.0 - backlogged url implement

Test results and supporting details
